<CONTENT id="_3793151_1"><TITLE value="Session 11"/><TITLECOLOR value="#000000"/><DESCRIPTION
   value=""/><BODY><TEXT>&lt;h4&gt;&lt;img src="@X@EmbeddedFile.requestUrlStub@X@bbcswebdav/xid-46884687_1" alt="" width="400" height="377" style="border: 0px solid #000000;"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h4&gt;Introduction&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;div&gt;This is the final session on investigating techniques for protecting an organisation's data.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;During this session we will focus on the review of our systems and processes for protecting the data.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;News&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2024/many-employees-just-don-t-care-about-company-security.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM23830" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Many employees just don’t care about company security | Information Age | ACS&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2024/cyber-security-governance-principles-refreshed.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM24400" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Cyber Security &lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Governance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; Principles refreshed | Information Age | ACS&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;a href="https://ia.acs.org.au/article/2024/australians-losing--significantly-more--to-fake-invoice-scams.html?ref=newsletter&amp;amp;deliveryName=DM21352" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Australians losing 'significantly more' to fake invoice scams | Information Age | ACS&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h5 id="anonymous_element_24"&gt;Topic&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Examine methods used to protect an organisation’s data (Data Protection)&lt;br&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 13.3333px;"&gt;Cyber Security Incident Response plan: Read this introduction page &lt;span style="font-size: 12pt;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.cyber.gov.au/report-and-recover/cyber-security-incident-response-plan" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;Cyber Security Incident Response Plan | Cyber.gov.au&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;policies,&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;processes and&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;systems&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Out of Session Activity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Revise today's presentation topics .&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;div&gt;Look at the Crown Resorts potential data breach, and consider the ramifications for customers.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Think about what Crown Resorts should do now?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;h5&gt;Portfolio Tasks&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;div&gt;Check assessments tab.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Complete outstanding work&lt;/div&gt;</TEXT><TYPE
